    "headerDoc": "STEP 974 — Sierpinski / Riesel Numbers: Computational Scaffolding\n  藤本伸樹 2026-04-22\n\n  Pattern C gap fill (2026-04-22 research radar audit):\n\n  Sierpinski number k: odd k ≥ 1 s.t. k · 2^n + 1 is composite for all n ≥ 1.\n  Selfridge 1962: k = 78557 is Sierpinski via covering set {3,5,7,13,19,37,73}.\n  Sierpinski problem: is 78557 the smallest? As of 2024, 5 candidates remain\n  (PrimeGrid project). Literature runs under \"covering congruence\" (radar gap).\n\n  Riesel number k (dual): odd k ≥ 1 s.t. k · 2^n - 1 is composite for all n ≥ 1.\n  Riesel 1956: k = 509203 conjectured smallest. 42+ candidate"
